  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preparedness and Response to Communities Affected by Disasters in Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As displaced communities in Cabo Delgado and Nampula remain vulnerable to natural disasters and conflict, IOM&apos;s intervention directly contributes to increase the preparedness future disasters through pre-positioning of non-food item (NFI) stock and strengthening of the assessment capacity for natural disaster risk analysis and data made available through the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) in Cabo Delgado. In light of the global COVID-19 pandemic, and the large-scale migratory in-flow of Mozambicans workers returning from South Africa, Zimbabwe, and other neighbouring countries, as a result of lock-downs or other restrictive policies, a crisis modifier will enable IOM to quickly activate and deploy resources at key border crossing points, return communities and, to the extent possible, in internal displaced person&apos;s settlement in central areas of the country, in efforts to prevent and mitigate associated risks of communal transmission.</narrative>
  </description>
